{
  "text": "With its high mass resolving power (> 400,000; i.e. ratio of ion mass to smallest separable ion mass difference), ultrahigh resolution Fourier transform ion cyclotron resonance mass spectrometry (FT-ICR-MS) is a powerful analytical method for resolving single mass formulas in the complex mixture of DOM [CITATION_1] . The application of this technique has led to an increased understanding of the processing of DOM in the ocean (e.g. [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] and in estuaries (e.g. [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . Other studies linked 20 optical and chemical DOM properties [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] .",
